<h2>Documentation</h2>

<p>Documentation is included in the R package. You can get help for a command by typing <tt>?&lt;command&gt;</tt> (e.g. <tt>?getAttractors</tt>) inside R when the package is loaded.</p>

<p>Additionally, a step-by-step tutorial is available <a href="files/BoolNet_package_vignette.pdf">here</a>.</p>

<p>A description of methods and algorithms can be accessed <a href="files/BoolNet_methods.pdf">here</a>.</p>

<h2>Software</h2>

<h3>Download</h3>

<p>BoolNet is available at <a href="http://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/BoolNet/index.html">CRAN</a>.</p>
<p>Alternatively, you can download the source package for manual installation <a href="files/BoolNet_1.4.tar.gz">here</a>.</p>

<h3>Installation</h3>

<h4>CRAN (all systems)</h4>
<p>In an R console, type <tt>install.packages()</tt>. In the menu that appears, choose a mirror, and select the package BoolNet. The package is now installed and can be loaded via <tt>library(BoolNet)</tt></p>



<p>If not downloaded from CRAN, the package has to be installed manually using <tt>R CMD INSTALL</tt>:</p>

<h4>Manual installation on Windows</h4>

<ul>
<li>Download the source package <a href="files/BoolNet_1.4.tar.gz">BoolNet_1.4.tar.gz</a>.</li>
<li>First, ensure that R-tools are installed. If this is not the case, download the version matching your R installation at <a href="http://www.murdoch-sutherland.com/Rtools/">http://www.murdoch-sutherland.com/Rtools/</a> and install it.</li>
<li>Open the Windows command prompt which is located in the "Accessories" folder of the start menu.</li>
<li>Type <tt>"&lt;Path-to-R&gt;\bin\R" CMD INSTALL "&lt;Path-to-Package&gt;\BoolNet_1.4.tar.gz"</tt> with the paths in <tt>&lt;&gt;</tt> set accordingly.</li>
<li>You can now start R and load the package with the command<br/>
	<tt>library(BoolNet)</tt></li>
</ul>
	
<h4>Manual installation on Linux, Unix, and Mac OS</h4>

On these systems, the package is built from the source.

<ul>
<li>Download the source package <a href="files/BoolNet_1.4.tar.gz">BoolNet_1.4.tar.gz</a>.</li>
<li>On Mac OS, ensure that XCode Tools are installed.</li>
<li>Open a root shell, and change to the folder where the package is located.</li>
<li>Type <tt>R CMD INSTALL BoolNet_1.4.tar.gz</tt></li>
<li>You can now start R and load the package with the command<br/>
	<tt>library(BoolNet)</tt></li>
</ul>

<h4>igraph</h4>
For some of the plots, the <tt>igraph</tt> package is required. This package is available <a href="http://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/igraph/index.html">at CRAN</a>.

<h4>XML</h4>
For the BioTapestry import, the <tt>XML</tt> package is required. This package is available <a href="http://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/XML/index.html">at CRAN</a> as well.

